Python Project â€“ CI Pipeline


ðŸ”¹ Step 1: Create a Python app with test

mkdir python-ci-demo
cd python-ci-demo
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install pytest

Create test file:
# app.py
def add(x, y):
    return x + y

# test_app.py
from app import add

def test_add():
    assert add(2, 3) == 5


ðŸ”¹ Step 2: Create GitHub Actions Workflow

Create file: .github/workflows/python-ci.yml

name: Python CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [ "main" ]

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3

      - name: Set up Python
        uses: actions/setup-python@v4
        with:
          python-version: '3.10'

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: |
          python -m pip install --upgrade pip
          pip install pytest

      - name: Run tests
        run: pytest

âœ… Result:
After pushing code to GitHub:

GitHub Actions triggers the workflow.

Tests run automatically.

You can view test output in the Actions tab of your repo.
